The course introduces the student to the law of foreign investment protection, a branch of international law based on bilateral and multilateral agreements concluded between states for the encouragement and protection of foreign investment. These agreements provide special protection for foregin investors and allow investors to bring claims directly against host states in arbitration independently from domestic court systems. It is one of the fastest growing, most practical, but also controversial branches of international law. As part of the course, we will analyze the states' substantive obligations to investors, procedures for settlement of investment disputes, and the interaction between investment protection law, domestic law and other branches of international law.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course aims to introduce the student to the main principles of international law of foreign investment and the investor-state dispute settlement mechanism.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course, the student  - recognizes the main principles and concepts of international law of foreign investment; - understands the procedure of settlement of investor-state disputes; - discusses the topical issues in investor-state dispute settlement.
